Structs/RPCAttributes/GRPCAttributes/Nes.name: statusCode
Structs/RPCAttributes/GRPCAttributes/Nes.abstract: The numeric status code of the gRPC request.

Structs/RPCAttributes/NestedSpanAttribut.name: system
Structs/RPCAttributes/NestedSpanAttribut.abstract: A string identifying the remoting system, e.g., “grpc”, “java_rmi” or “wcf”.

Structs/RPCAttributes/NestedSpanAttribut.name: service
Structs/RPCAttributes/NestedSpanAttribut.abstract: The full name of the service being called, including its package name, if applicable.

Structs/RPCAttributes/NestedSpanAttribut.name: method
Structs/RPCAttributes/NestedSpanAttribut.abstract: The name of the method being called, must be equal to the $method part in the span name.

Structs/RPCAttributes/GRPCAttributes.htm.name: GRPCAttributes
Structs/RPCAttributes/GRPCAttributes.htm.abstract: Semantic concentions for gRPC spans as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/PeerAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: service
Structs/PeerAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The service.name of the remote service. SHOULD be equal to the actual service.name resource attribute of the remote service if any.

Structs/NetAttributes/HostAttributes/Nes.name: ip
Structs/NetAttributes/HostAttributes/Nes.abstract: Like peer.ip but for the host IP. Useful in case of a multi-IP host.

Structs/NetAttributes/PeerAttributes/Nes.name: ip
Structs/NetAttributes/PeerAttributes/Nes.abstract: Remote address of the peer (dotted decimal for IPv4 or RFC5952 for IPv6).

Structs/NetAttributes/PeerAttributes/Nes.name: port
Structs/NetAttributes/PeerAttributes/Nes.abstract: Remote port number as an integer. E.g., 80.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.name: messageKey
Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.abstract: Message keys in Kafka are used for grouping alike messages to ensure they’re processed on the same partition.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.name: consumerGroup
Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.abstract: Name of the Kafka Consumer Group that is handling the message. Only applies to consumers, not producers.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.name: clientID
Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.abstract: Client Id for the Consumer or Producer that is handling the message.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.name: tombstone
Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.abstract: A boolean that is true if the message is a tombstone.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: destination
Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: The message destination name. This might be equal to the span name but is required nevertheless.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: tempDestination
Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: A boolean that is true if the message destination is temporary.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: messageID
Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: A value used by the messaging system as an identifier for the message, represented as a string.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: conversationID
Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: The conversation ID identifying the conversation to which the message belongs, represented as a string. Sometimes called “Correlation ID”.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: messagePayloadSizeBytes
Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: The (uncompressed) size of the message payload in bytes. Also use this attribute if it is unknown whether the compressed or uncompressed

Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: messagePayloadCompressedSizeBytes
Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: The compressed size of the message payload in bytes.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: operation
Structs/MessagingAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: A string identifying the kind of message consumption as defined in the Operation names section.

Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.name: KafkaAttributes
Structs/MessagingAttributes/KafkaAttribu.abstract: Semantic conventions for Kafka spans as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/HTTPAttributes/ServerAttributes/.name: name
Structs/HTTPAttributes/ServerAttributes/.abstract: The primary server name of the matched virtual host. This should be obtained via configuration.

Structs/HTTPAttributes/ServerAttributes/.name: clientIP
Structs/HTTPAttributes/ServerAttributes/.abstract: The IP address of the original client behind all proxies, if known (e.g. from X-Forwarded-For).

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: url
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: Full HTTP request URL in the form scheme://host[:port]/path?query[#fragment].

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: target
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The full request target as passed in a HTTP request line or equivalent, e.g. “/path/12314/?q=ddds#123”.

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: host
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The value of the HTTP host header. When the header is empty or not present, this attribute should be the same.

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: scheme
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The URI scheme identifying the used protocol: “http” or “https”

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: userAgent
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: Value of the HTTP User-Agent header sent by the client.

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: requestContentLength
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The size of the request payload body in bytes. This is the number of bytes transferred excluding headers and is often,

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: requestContentLengthUncompressed
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The size of the uncompressed request payload body after transport decoding. Not set if transport encoding not used.

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: responseContentLength
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The size of the response payload body in bytes. This is the number of bytes transferred excluding headers and

Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: responseContentLengthUncompressed
Structs/HTTPAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The size of the uncompressed response payload body after transport decoding. Not set if transport encoding not used.

Structs/HTTPAttributes/ServerAttributes..name: ServerAttributes
Structs/HTTPAttributes/ServerAttributes..abstract: Semantic conventions for HTTP Server spans as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.name: collection
Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.abstract: The name of the source on which the triggering operation was performed.

Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.name: operation
Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.abstract: Describes the type of the operation that was performed on the data. See OpenTelemetry: Operation Type for possible values.

Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.name: time
Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.abstract: A string containing the time when the data was accessed in the

Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.name: name
Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.abstract: The document name/table subjected to the operation. For example, in Cloud Storage or S3 is the name of the file,

Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: trigger
Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: Type of the trigger on which the function is executed. See OpenTelemetry: Function Trigger Type for possible values.

Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: execution
Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The execution ID of the current function execution.

Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: time
Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: A string containing the function invocation time in the

Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: cron
Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: A string containing the schedule period as Cron Expression.

Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: coldstart
Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: A boolean that is true if the serverless function is executed for the first time (aka cold-start).

Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: invokedProvider
Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The cloud provider of the invoked function.

Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.name: invokedRegion
Structs/FaaSAttributes/NestedSpanAttribu.abstract: The cloud region of the invoked function.

Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.name: DocumentAttributes
Structs/FaaSAttributes/DocumentAttribute.abstract: Semantic Convention for FaaS triggered as a response to some data source operation such as a database or filesystem read/write.

Structs/ExceptionAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: type
Structs/ExceptionAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: The type of the exception (its fully-qualified class name, if applicable). The dynamic type of the exception should

Structs/ExceptionAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: stacktrace
Structs/ExceptionAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: A stacktrace as a string in the natural representation for the language runtime. The representation is to be determined

Structs/ExceptionAttributes/NestedSpanAt.name: escaped
Structs/ExceptionAttributes/NestedSpanAt.abstract: SHOULD be set to true if the exception event is recorded at a point where it is known that the exception

Structs/EndUserAttributes/NestedSpanAttr.name: id
Structs/EndUserAttributes/NestedSpanAttr.abstract: Username or client_id extracted from the access token or Authorization header in the inbound request from outside the system.

Structs/EndUserAttributes/NestedSpanAttr.name: role
Structs/EndUserAttributes/NestedSpanAttr.abstract: Actual/assumed role the client is making the request under extracted from token or application security context.

Structs/EndUserAttributes/NestedSpanAttr.name: scope
Structs/EndUserAttributes/NestedSpanAttr.abstract: Scopes or granted authorities the client currently possesses extracted from token or application security context.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/SQLAttributes.name: table
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/SQLAttributes.abstract: The name of the primary table that the operation is acting upon, including the schema name (if applicable).

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/MongoDBAttrib.name: collection
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/MongoDBAttrib.abstract: The collection being accessed within the database stated in db.name.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/RedisAttribut.name: databaseIndex
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/RedisAttribut.abstract: The index of the database being accessed as used in the SELECT command,

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/CassandraAttr.name: keyspace
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/CassandraAttr.abstract: The name of the keyspace being accessed. To be used instead of the generic db.name attribute.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/NestedSpanAtt.name: system
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/NestedSpanAtt.abstract: An identifier for the database management system (DBMS) product being used. See OpenTelemetry: Database attributes for a list of well-known identifiers.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/NestedSpanAtt.name: connectionString
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/NestedSpanAtt.abstract: The connection string used to connect to the database. It is recommended to remove embedded credentials.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/NestedSpanAtt.name: operation
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/NestedSpanAtt.abstract: The name of the operation being executed, e.g. the MongoDB command name

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/MSSQLAttribut.name: MSSQLAttributes
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/MSSQLAttribut.abstract: Semantic conventions for MSSQL client calls as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/CassandraAttr.name: CassandraAttributes
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/CassandraAttr.abstract: Semantic conventions for Cassandra client calls as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/HBaseAttribut.name: HBaseAttributes
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/HBaseAttribut.abstract: Semantic conventions for HBase client calls as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/RedisAttribut.name: RedisAttributes
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/RedisAttribut.abstract: Semantic conventions for Redis client calls as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/MongoDBAttrib.abstract: Semantic conventions for MongoDB client calls as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes/SQLAttributes.name: SQLAttributes
Structs/DatabaseAttributes/SQLAttributes.abstract: Semantic conventions for SQL client calls as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/DatabaseAttributes.html.abstract: Semantic conventions for database client calls as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.

Structs/HTTPAttributes.html.abstract: Semantic conventions for HTTP spans as defined in the OpenTelemetry spec.
